==English==
===Alternate spellings===
*[[whobub]] (''obsolete'')

===Etymology===
Perhaps from Irish; compare Irish ''[[ababú]]!'' (a battle-cry), Gaelic ''[[ub|ub! ub!]]'' (expressing contempt, etc.), ''[[ubh ubh]]!'' (expressing disgust).

===Noun===
'''hubbub'''
# a [[confuse]]d [[uproar]], [[commotion]], [[tumult]] or [[racket]]

